Well, you'll have to find the time.

1129
01:24:09,272 --> 01:24:11,774
Look they don't sentence picture
directors to a place like this...

1130
01:24:11,775 --> 01:24:13,777
for a little disagreement
with a yard bull.

1131
01:24:13,778 --> 01:24:15,780
- Don't they?
- No.

1132
01:24:15,780 --> 01:24:17,782
Oh.

1133
01:24:17,783 --> 01:24:20,352
- Well, then, maybe you
ain't a movie director.
- Huh?

1134
01:24:20,353 --> 01:24:22,355
Maybe that idea
just come to you...

1135
01:24:22,355 --> 01:24:25,660
- when you got hit on the head, maybe.
- Now, look--

1136
01:24:25,660 --> 01:24:29,097
We used to have a fella here
once that thought he was Lindbergh.

1137
01:24:29,098 --> 01:24:32,168
He used to fly away
every night...

1138
01:24:32,168 --> 01:24:35,639
but he was always
back in the morning.

1139
01:24:35,640 --> 01:24:38,176
Don't I look like
a picture director?

1140
01:24:38,176 --> 01:24:40,178
'Course I never seen one.

1141
01:24:40,179 --> 01:24:44,173
You look more like a soda jerk,
or maybe a plasterer, maybe.

1142
01:24:45,152 --> 01:24:48,322
But--

1143
01:24:48,323 --> 01:24:51,927
- If ever a plot need a twist,
this one does.
- Huh?

1144
01:24:51,928 --> 01:24:54,331
- I gotta get my picture in the paper.
- That would be swell.

1145
01:24:54,331 --> 01:24:56,333
Then you could paste it
over your bunk.

1146
01:24:56,334 --> 01:24:58,936
What kind of people get
their pictures in the paper?

1147
01:24:58,937 --> 01:25:02,074
Ball players?

1148
01:25:02,075 --> 01:25:04,077
Girls? They take 'em
with their legs crossed.

1149
01:25:04,077 --> 01:25:08,071
I cut one out once. She had a--
She was sitting-- No?

1150
01:25:09,084 --> 01:25:12,220
When you die,
if you was important enough.

1151
01:25:12,221 --> 01:25:14,357
I've had that.

1152
01:25:14,357 --> 01:25:16,359
Murderers?

1153
01:25:16,360 --> 01:25:19,229
There was a swell picture
of a friend of mine.

1154
01:25:19,230 --> 01:25:21,232
He was a lodge brother.

1155
01:25:21,233 --> 01:25:24,036
They called him
''the blowtorch killer.''

1156
01:25:24,036 --> 01:25:27,674
That's it. That's it!

1157
01:25:27,675 --> 01:25:30,244
You tell the Mister I'm ready
to make a full confession.

1158
01:25:30,244 --> 01:25:32,279
- Now, wait a minute.
- Come on.

1159
01:25:32,280 --> 01:25:34,282
- Now, take it easy.
- There isn't a moment to lose.

1160
01:25:34,283 --> 01:25:36,285
- Now, look--
- I'm-- My conscience has got me.

1161
01:25:36,285 --> 01:25:39,188
- You're gonna get--
- I want to confess to the murder
ofJohn L. Sullivan.

1162
01:25:39,189 --> 01:25:41,925
- Wait a minute!
- I killed John L. Sullivan!

1163
01:25:41,926 --> 01:25:45,920
- I killed John L. Sullivan!
- I'm telling you,
you're doing the wrong thing.

1164
01:25:46,198 --> 01:25:48,367
- I'm a murderer!
- Will you listen to me
before somebody--

1165
01:25:48,368 --> 01:25:50,370
I killed John L. Sullivan!

1166
01:25:50,371 --> 01:25:54,365
[ Both Talking ]

1167
01:26:05,957 --> 01:26:09,951
[ Shouts ]

1168
01:26:11,999 --> 01:26:15,993
[ No Audio ]

1169
01:26:32,492 --> 01:26:36,486
[ No Audio ]

1170
01:26:43,474 --> 01:26:47,468
[ No Audio ]

1171
01:26:53,820 --> 01:26:57,814
[ No Audio ]

1172
01:27:15,249 --> 01:27:19,243
[ Clamoring ]

1173
01:27:30,935 --> 01:27:34,606
- I'm so happy.
- So am I!

1174
01:27:34,607 --> 01:27:37,577
- I said, I'm so happy!
- What?

1175
01:27:37,577 --> 01:27:39,579
Your wife got married last week.

1176
01:27:39,580 --> 01:27:41,582
Who got buried last week?

1177
01:27:41,583 --> 01:27:45,154
She got married last week!

1178
01:27:45,154 --> 01:27:47,590
My wife?
You say they buried her?

1179
01:27:47,591 --> 01:27:50,895
No, she got married.
She married your business manager.

1180
01:27:50,895 --> 01:27:53,031
- She married him?
- Yes!

1181
01:27:53,031 --> 01:27:55,033
- He married her?
- Yes!

1182
01:27:55,034 --> 01:27:57,169
- But how?
- Because you were dead.

1183
01:27:57,170 --> 01:27:59,172
- Dead?
- Dead.

1184
01:27:59,172 --> 01:28:03,166
[ People Talking ]

1185
01:28:04,446 --> 01:28:06,448
- Do you suppose she'll
give you a divorce?
- Give it to me?

1186
01:28:06,448 --> 01:28:08,617
She'll beg me for it.
Don't you understand?
She's got to give it to me.

1187
01:28:08,618 --> 01:28:10,620
Otherwise it's bigamy,
unfaithfulness,

1188
01:28:10,621 --> 01:28:13,190
alienation of affection,
corpus delicti.

1189
01:28:13,190 --> 01:28:15,893
[ All Talking ]

1190
01:28:15,894 --> 01:28:18,630
- And then you'll be free.
- Then I'll be free.

1191
01:28:18,631 --> 01:28:20,633
But not for long, I hope.

1192
01:28:20,634 --> 01:28:23,637
- [ All Talking ]
-Just a moment, gentlemen!

1193
01:28:23,638 --> 01:28:25,940
Sully, I just want to tell you that
O Brother, Where Art Thou?

1194
01:28:25,940 --> 01:28:28,076
is gonna be the greatest
tragedy ever made.

1195
01:28:28,077 --> 01:28:30,279
- Well, I--
- The world will weep!
Humanity will sob.

1196
01:28:30,280 --> 01:28:32,315
It'll put Shakespeare
back with the shipping news.

1197
01:28:32,315 --> 01:28:34,317
Quiet! Your personal courage,
your sacrifice...

1198
01:28:34,318 --> 01:28:36,587
the lengths to which you went to sample
the bitter dregs of vicissitude...

1199
01:28:36,588 --> 01:28:38,590
will make O Brother, Where Art Thou?
positively--

1200
01:28:38,590 --> 01:28:40,592
- I'm sorry to disappoint you.
- You're sorry to disappoint me?

1201
01:28:40,593 --> 01:28:42,595
Yes, and I say it
with some embarrassment,

1202
01:28:42,596 --> 01:28:45,466
but I don't want to make
O Brother, Where Art Thou?

1203
01:28:45,466 --> 01:28:47,468
You don't want to make
O Brother, Where Art Thou?

1204
01:28:47,469 --> 01:28:50,105
No. I say it with some embarrassment.
I want to make a comedy.

1205
01:28:50,106 --> 01:28:52,341
You say it with some embarrassment?

1206
01:28:52,342 --> 01:28:54,978
He doesn't want to make
O Brother, Where Art Thou?
He wants to make a comedy.

1207
01:28:54,978 --> 01:28:57,681
He don't mean that, boss.
He's still a little stir crazy.

1208
01:28:57,682 --> 01:29:00,018
- Oh, yes, I do. Oh, no I'm not!
- You're joking, aren't you?

1209
01:29:00,019 --> 01:29:02,021
- It's in bad taste, but it's a joke?
- No.

1210
01:29:02,021 --> 01:29:04,523
But it's had more publicity
than the Johnstown flood.

1211
01:29:04,524 --> 01:29:07,193
- What are we gonna do?
- Oh, brother.

1212
01:29:07,194 --> 01:29:10,197
Why don't you want to make
O Brother, Where Art Thou, Sully?

1213
01:29:10,198 --> 01:29:13,937
In the first place, I'm too happy
to make O Brother, Where Art Thou?

1214
01:29:13,937 --> 01:29:17,274
In the second place,
I haven't suffered enough to make
O Brother, Where Art Thou?

1215
01:29:17,274 --> 01:29:20,277
- You haven't suffered enough?
- He hasn't suffered enough?

1216
01:29:20,278 --> 01:29:22,948
- But Sully!
- I'll tell you something else.

1217
01:29:22,949 --> 01:29:25,518
There's a lot to be said
for making people laugh.

1218
01:29:25,519 --> 01:29:28,221
Did you know that's all
some people have?

1219
01:29:28,222 --> 01:29:32,216
It isn't much, but it's better
than nothing in this cockeyed caravan.

1220
01:29:34,596 --> 01:29:36,732
Boy.

1221
01:29:36,733 --> 01:29:40,727
[ Laughing ]

1222
01:30:39,816 --> 01:30:43,810
You see? You see
the symbolism of it?

